# Tailwind CSS v4

## Font Loading

**Never** use `@import url("https://fonts.googleapis.com/...")` in `globals.css` with Tailwind v4. The `@tailwindcss/postcss` plugin inlines Tailwind as `@layer` blocks, which pushes any remaining CSS `@import url()` after those layers — invalid per CSS spec.

**Always** load fonts via `next/font/google` in `app/layout.tsx`:

```tsx
import { Inter, JetBrains_Mono } from "next/font/google";

const inter = Inter({ subsets: ["latin"], variable: "--font-inter", display: "swap" });
const jetbrainsMono = JetBrains_Mono({ subsets: ["latin"], variable: "--font-jetbrains-mono", display: "swap" });

// In JSX:
<html className={`dark ${inter.variable} ${jetbrainsMono.variable}`}>
```

Then reference them as CSS variables in `tailwind.config.ts`:
```ts
fontFamily: {
  sans: ["var(--font-inter)", "system-ui", "sans-serif"],
  mono: ["var(--font-jetbrains-mono)", "monospace"],
}
```

## Import Syntax

```css
/* ✅ v4 — correct: all @import rules MUST come before @layer (which Tailwind generates) */
@import url("https://fonts.googleapis.com/...");  /* external fonts first */
@import "tailwindcss";
@config "../tailwind.config.ts";

/* ❌ v3 — forbidden */
@tailwind base;
@tailwind components;
@tailwind utilities;

/* ❌ font import AFTER tailwindcss — causes "must precede all rules" parse error */
@import "tailwindcss";
@import url("https://fonts.googleapis.com/...");
```

> CSS rule: all `@import` statements must precede `@layer` and other rules. `@import "tailwindcss"` expands into `@layer` blocks during PostCSS processing, so any `@import url(...)` after it is illegal.

## PostCSS Config

```js
// ✅ v4 — no autoprefixer needed (built-in)
plugins: { "@tailwindcss/postcss": {} }

// ❌ autoprefixer is redundant and causes errors in v4
plugins: { "@tailwindcss/postcss": {}, "autoprefixer": {} }
```

## Custom Theme (tailwind.config.ts)

Keep theme customization in `tailwind.config.ts` under `theme.extend`. The `@config` directive in `globals.css` loads it. Do NOT duplicate tokens in both the config and `@theme {}` blocks.

## Animations

Custom animations are defined in `tailwind.config.ts` under `theme.extend.animation` and `theme.extend.keyframes`. Do NOT install `tailwindcss-animate` — it is not v4 compatible and is unused in this project.

## Class Utilities

Always use `cn()` from `lib/utils.ts`:

```tsx
// ✅
className={cn("base-class", condition && "conditional-class", className)}

// ❌
className={`base-class ${condition ? "conditional-class" : ""}`}
```

## Design Token Usage

Custom colors (`matrix-green`, `aquamarine`, `surface`, `subtle`, `text-muted`, `text-neon`) are defined in `tailwind.config.ts` and usable as standard Tailwind classes:

```tsx
// ✅ Use semantic tokens
className="bg-surface border-subtle text-text-muted text-matrix-green"

// ❌ Raw hex values in className
className="bg-[#12161A]"
```
